description.narrative:
- Stakeholders' impacts: i) benefits to soybean and sunflower farmers who will secure a reliable access to market, and ii) benefits to the end consumers who benefit from improved food security as a result of larger volumes of oilseeds (+900,000 metric tons) and their derivatives brought to market;
- Support the Competitiveness of an Export-Oriented Sector in Argentina: as Argentina slowly reengages with the global capital markets, IFC's support to Vicentin should send positive signal to other investors about the strong prospects and solid fundaments of the oilseeds sector in Argentina, which is globally competitive and relevant in the international markets;
- Environmental and Social Standards: IFC investment is expected to further enhance Vicentin's E&S performance in a number of areas by setting performance indicators and targets.

